"{\"uid\": \"dailyrecord.co.uk-tv-bbc-presenter-halts-olympic-coverage-33341856\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Spectators watching the BBC's coverage of the Olympic Games 2024 could not believe their eyes as the programme was hilariously interrupted by window cleaners.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those tuned in for the Paris 2024 excitement on Saturday saw presenter Hazel Irvine and diving expert Tonia Couch discussing the events when suddenly two men appeared outside.\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6955553233555427e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvine_Transportation_Center\", \"score\": 0.9573557339216668, \"rank\": 0.0445372768425827, \"text\": \"Irvine\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvine_Transportation_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvine_Transportation_Center\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonia_Couch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tonia Couch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonia_Couch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tonia_Couch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quick on her feet, Hazel made light of the surprise cameo, joking: \\\"Can you see this behind me?\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because we have got two gentlemen fixing our studio.\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think they know they are on telly at the moment,\\\" as reported by the Mirror.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Oblivious to their newfound fame, the cleaners continued with their task, inadvertently stealing the spotlight and prompting viewers to take to Twitter to express their delight.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 717, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.110920447696425e-24, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The impromptu appearance sparked a flurry of tweets as the window-cleaning duo became an instant hit.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One entertained viewer tweeted: \\\"Live Olympic window cleaning on the BBC!\\\"\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"while another added: \\\"Window cleaners have just turned up on the BBC coverage.\\\"\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A third commented: \\\"Just a casual bit of window cleaning in the middle of the BBC coverage.\\\"\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another noted: \\\"The rain is still TIPPING down in Paris.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 1.0319682845956896e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And now the BBC has had to get the window cleaners in whilst they are on air.\\\"\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1172, \"end\": 1175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet another Twitter user joked: \\\"I did not know window cleaning now qualified as an Olympic sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.110920447696425e-24, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"GB News presenter Martin Daubney faced another blunder this week, following an awkward start to his news hour.\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GB_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GB News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GB_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GB_News\"}, {\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999918503313106, \"rank\": 8.142243798631756e-06, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a decision that failed to win over viewers, BBC producers chose to use green screen technology to craft a backdrop for an early morning chat show delivered by Jeanette Kwakye, with guests including JJ Chalmers and Fred Sirieix.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1504, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9988697964456055, \"rank\": 0.0010190835505433592, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1619, \"end\": 1634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Kwakye\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeanette Kwakye\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Kwakye\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Kwakye\"}, {\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Sirieix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Confusingly, a digitally-constructed city courtyard was used as the setting for their discussion.\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans were quick to voice their disappointment with the arrangement, given that the show is filmed in central Paris in a studio that boasts views of the iconic Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1896, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 1.0319682845956896e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One annoyed viewer took to the internet to air their grievances, posting: \\\"This green screen stuff is horrific.\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stop it.\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have got a studio in Paris looking at the Eiffel Tower ffs.\\\"\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2107, \"end\": 2112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 1.0319682845956896e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(sic).\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"AtReach and across our entitieswe and our partners use information collected through cookies and other identifiers from your device to improve experience on our site, analyse how it is used and to show personalised advertising.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can opt out of the sale or sharing of your data, at any time clicking the \\\"Do Not Sell or Share my Data\\\" button at the bottom of the webpage.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please note that your preferences are browser specific.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": []}, {\"